I went to the Popeyes located at 2010 86th Street in Brooklyn NY and ordered a Chicken Sandwich (classic) with NO MAYO. When I left and drove to my destination I opened up the packaging and the sandwich had MAYO on it. Im allergic to MAYO and i am glad i checked the sandwich before consuming it. I am an essential worker in New York City and the little bit of time I was alloted to get something to eat, I chose this franchise to get something, and one of my favorite sandwiches.  I was highly displeased with the service I received. The packaging even had the NO MAYO label on it but the sandwich contained MAYO. I'm still baffled as to how I can specifically order an sandwich and ask for NO MAYO and the packaging stated it doesn't have MAYO, but it in fact does. I wasted a large portion of my break driving to the restaurant and waiting for my order and unable to consume what I purchased. The only thing I am grateful for was checking my order before I engulfed or else I could be hospitalized right now. The carelessness and lack of attention to detail is very bothersome. I have photographs as well.

(Translated by Google) The decoration is average, it looks clean and hygienic, the light is a bit soft, and there is a gourmet area. There is no coffee, only fast food restaurants often use beverage machines for drinks. A drink, a recommended pie, and four spicy fried chicken. The drinks from the beverage machine taste the same there. STRAWBERRY PIE is beautifully packaged, there is no freshly fried crispy in the mouth, and the taste is okay. The marinating method of fried chicken nuggets is a bit like Chinese style. When they are first fried, they look brownish-yellow. Perhaps Westerners like this color, but it should be golden in China. The fried chicken nuggets are crispy on the outside and juicy on the inside. The taste is salty from the outside to the inside. The outside is a little saltier and the inside is lighter. It is delicious for those who like salty food. Perhaps fried chicken nuggets are the specialty of this store, and the price is moderate.  (Original) 装修一般，看上去干净卫生，光线有点柔，有美食享用区。 没有咖啡，只有快餐店常概饮料机饮料。 要一杯饮料，一块推荐的派，四块辣味炸鸡。 饮料机的饮料味道那儿都一样。 STRAWBERRY PIE 包装美观，入口时没有刚炸出来的香酥，味道还可以。 炸鸡块腌制方法有点像中国风味，刚炸出来时外表看上去褐黄色，或许西方人喜欢这种颜色，在中国应该是金黄色。炸鸡块入口时外皮香酥内多汁，味道是由外到内渗透出咸香味，外面咸一点，里面淡一点，对于喜欢咸香味美食的人来说美味。 或许炸鸡块就是这店的特色，价格适中。
